---
// src/components/chrome/Breadcrumb.astro ‚Äî M-UX T3 deliverable.
//
// Per ADR-0002 (https://.../adr/0002_ux_layer_mdn_three_column.md)
// and design_docs/architecture.md ¬ß1.6, the top breadcrumb is the
// secondary navigation surface ‚Äî a sticky `<nav>` that hosts:
//   1. the path indicator (cs-300 / Lectures / ch_4 ‚Äî ‚Ä¶),
//   2. the collection switcher (Lectures / Notes / Practice pills),
//   3. prev/next chapter buttons.
//
// This component mounts into the `breadcrumb` slot declared by
// `src/layouts/Base.astro` (T1) and renders on every chapter route
// (lectures, notes, practice). T7 added the `drawer-trigger` named
// slot (per MUX-BO-ISS-04 + DA3-B + DA2-F): the hamburger button
// from `Drawer.astro` lands here so the breadcrumb's flexbox layout
// owns its placement. The slot is rendered inside `.breadcrumb`'s
// flex row, ahead of the path indicator, so on narrow widths the
// hamburger sits at the leading edge. Visibility is gated via CSS
// `@media (max-width: 1023.98px)` on the button itself (T7).
//
// Contract (per T3 spec):
//   - Pure SSR. No JS required for navigation. Sticky behaviour is
//     pure CSS but lives on the OUTER slot wrapper
//     (`<nav data-slot="breadcrumb">` in Base.astro) ‚Äî see Base.astro's
//     `.chrome > [data-slot="breadcrumb"] { position: sticky; ... }`
//     rule. T8 cycle 1 moved sticky out of this inner nav per
//     M-UX-T3-ISS-01: the inner nav's containing block was its own
//     slot wrapper at the wrapper's auto-sized height ‚Äî zero stick
//     range. The slot wrapper is a direct grid child of `.chrome`
//     (which has `min-height: 100vh` + tall content), giving real
//     stick range. Verified via headless-browser scroll test in
//     `.smoke/screenshots/lectures-ch4-1280x800-midscroll-T3.png`.
//     The collection switcher and prev/next buttons are plain `<a>`
//     elements with computed hrefs.
//   - Path computed from `Astro.url.pathname`. Pattern:
//     `/{base}/{collection}/{chapter_id}/`. On non-chapter routes
//     this component is not mounted (chapter routes only ‚Äî the
//     index page does not include it).
//   - Prev/next ordered by `n` (chapter number) ‚Äî the cs-300 chapter
//     map skips ch_8 (no ch_8 row in `scripts/chapters.json`), so
//     ch_7's next is ch_9 by data, not slug-arithmetic.
//   - At chapter-list boundaries (ch_1 prev, last optional next),
//     the button renders as a non-link `<span>` with `aria-disabled`
//     so it remains visible but inert.
//
// BASE_URL convention (resolves MUX-BO-ISS-02 / HIGH-2 + MUX-BO-DA-1):
// every chapter / collection link is constructed via
// `import.meta.env.BASE_URL`; never hardcode `/DSA/`. Same convention
// as `src/components/chrome/LeftRail.astro` line 46 and
// `src/pages/index.astro` line 16. The audit grep
// (`grep -nE '/DSA/' Breadcrumb.astro`) is documented to allow
// `//`-comment hits per DA2-E / DA3-A reviewer-eyes policy ‚Äî this
// header references `/DSA/` only inside doc-comment lines.
//
// M-UX T9 update (2026-04-25): functional breadcrumb links per spec
// D4 + AC7/AC8/AC9. Three changes:
//   1. The `cs-300` root segment becomes a real `<a>` linking to
//      `${baseUrl}/` (home). Was a non-link `<span>` in the cycle-1
//      shell ‚Äî clicked text led nowhere.
//   2. The middle path segment (`Lectures` / `Notes` / `Practice`)
//      now links to the corresponding collection LANDING page
//      (`${baseUrl}/${collection}/`, T9 D5) ‚Äî was previously
//      hyperlinked to the same-collection chapter page (a no-op
//      navigation since the user was already on that page).
//   3. The current chapter title segment was already a `<span
//      aria-current="page">` (correct) ‚Äî preserved verbatim. The
//      AC9 assertion just verifies it stays that way.
// Collection-switcher pills + prev/next buttons untouched (T9 era).
//
// M-UX-REVIEW T4 update (2026-04-27): D1 (UI-review F9, HIGH) hides
// the breadcrumb bar entirely at <768px so the mobile chrome stack
// shrinks to {drawer-trigger, eyebrow, H1, collection-tabs,
// on-this-page details, content}. The hide is owned by Base.astro's
// `.breadcrumb-bar` rule on the outer slot wrapper (the inner `<nav
// class="breadcrumb">` that this file emits is a child of that
// wrapper, so display:none cascades). This file's only T4 change is
// removing the `drawer-trigger` named slot ‚Äî the trigger now mounts
// as a sibling of the breadcrumb in `Base.astro`'s new `drawer-
// trigger` slot so it survives the mobile breadcrumb hide. Per spec
// "Option A ‚Äî extract `DrawerTrigger.astro` from inside
// `Breadcrumb.astro` to be a sibling of the breadcrumb in
// `Base.astro`. At <768px the breadcrumb hides but the trigger stays
// visible at the top of the page." Cleaner than Option B's
// `display: contents` hack and gives the trigger a stable parent
// regardless of viewport. The prev/next chapter affordance loses its
// mobile placement; the drawer's chapter list IS the prev/next
// surface on mobile (acceptable per spec).
//
// M-UX-REVIEW T3 update (2026-04-27): D1 splits the breadcrumb bar.
// Three navigation models previously shared one row ‚Äî crumbs,
// chapter prev/next, and the collection switcher. Per UI-review F5
// (HIGH) the collection switcher now lives in a dedicated segmented-
// control row directly under the chapter H1 (`CollectionTabs.astro`,
// D2). Concrete shape changes here:
//   1. The collection-switcher `<ul class="collection-switcher">`
//      with three `<li class="collection-pill">` children is REMOVED
//      from the right-side `breadcrumb-controls` cluster. The
//      cross-collection link is preserved via the new tabs (visible
//      directly under the H1) AND the home page card layout
//      (T1 D1) ‚Äî see T3 spec "Out of scope" for the link-reachability
//      analysis. The T9 functional-test cases that asserted the
//      breadcrumb middle segment text + href (`breadcrumb-collection-
//      link-{lectures,notes,practice}`) are removed in the same
//      edit because their selectors no longer exist; new T3 tests
//      cover the same link contract on the tabs (`collection-tabs-
//      current-aria`, `collection-tabs-on-notes`).
//   2. The middle path segment (`<a>Lectures</a>` etc) is REMOVED
//      from the `<ol>` crumbs list. The user already knows which
//      collection they're in from the URL + the segmented control
//      under the H1; the redundant crumb is gone. Path now reads
//      `cs-300 / ch_4 ‚Äî ‚Ä¶`.
//   3. The chapter-button arrows change from `‚Äπ ch_3` / `ch_5 ‚Ä∫`
//      (text guillemets) to `‚Üê ch_3` / `ch_5 ‚Üí` (arrows). Per the
//      review's before/after mock ‚Äî same width, more readable on
//      mobile, more obviously navigational than guillemets.
// Result: row 1 carries crumbs + chapter prev/next (one model per
// side). Row 2 (the H1 + tabs) carries collection switching. The
// cross-collection link is preserved ‚Äî the `breadcrumb-controls`
// cluster collapses from {prev, switcher, next} to {prev, next}.
//
// Companion files:
//   - design_docs/milestones/m_ux_polish/tasks/T3_breadcrumb.md
//   - design_docs/milestones/m_ux_polish/tasks/T9_layout_polish.md (D4)
//   - design_docs/adr/0002_ux_layer_mdn_three_column.md
//   - src/layouts/Base.astro (T1 ‚Äî slot contract)
//   - src/components/chrome/LeftRail.astro (T2 ‚Äî sibling chrome)
//   - src/pages/{lectures,notes,practice}/index.astro (T9 ‚Äî link targets)
//   - scripts/chapters.json (chapter manifest; sort key `n`)
import chapters from '../../../scripts/chapters.json';

const baseUrl = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');

// Closed set per architecture.md ¬ß1.6 + ADR-0002 ‚Äî three collections.
// T3 (2026-04-27) trimmed `COLLECTIONS`, `COLLECTION_LABEL`, and the
// `collectionLandingHref` helper because the breadcrumb no longer
// renders a middle path segment or the collection switcher. The
// type alias stays for the URL-pattern parse + the prev/next chapter
// link helper. Collection labels live in `CollectionTabs.astro`
// (the new home for the cross-collection link).
type Collection = 'lectures' | 'notes' | 'practice';

// Sort by `n` so ch_10 lands after ch_9 (lexicographic on `id` would
// invert). Same key as LeftRail.astro line 51.
const sorted = [...chapters].sort((a, b) => a.n - b.n);

// Derive the current collection + chapter id from the URL. Chapter
// routes are `/{BASE_URL}/{collection}/{chapter-id}/`. Non-chapter
// routes return null on either field ‚Äî the component is only mounted
// on chapter routes, but defensive parsing keeps the build clean if a
// future caller mounts it elsewhere.
const path = Astro.url.pathname;
const match = path.match(/\/(lectures|notes|practice)\/(ch_\d+)\/?$/);
const currentCollection: Collection | null = match
  ? (match[1] as Collection)
  : null;
const currentChapterId = match ? match[2] : null;

const currentChapter = currentChapterId
  ? sorted.find((c) => c.id === currentChapterId)
  : null;

// Prev/next are by `n`-order index ‚Äî not slug-arithmetic. ch_7's next
// is ch_9 because that's what the manifest says (no ch_8 row).
const currentIndex = currentChapter
  ? sorted.findIndex((c) => c.id === currentChapter.id)
  : -1;
const prevChapter = currentIndex > 0 ? sorted[currentIndex - 1] : null;
const nextChapter =
  currentIndex >= 0 && currentIndex < sorted.length - 1
    ? sorted[currentIndex + 1]
    : null;

// Helper: build a same-collection chapter href. Now used only by the
// prev/next chapter buttons; the collection-switcher pills moved to
// `CollectionTabs.astro` (T3 D2) and own their own href helper.
function chapterHref(collection: Collection, chapterId: string): string {
  return `${baseUrl}/${collection}/${chapterId}/`;
}

// T9 D4 ‚Äî home href for the leading `cs-300` crumb. Trailing slash
// preserved so Astro's auto-route resolution doesn't 301 the link.
const homeHref = `${baseUrl}/`;
---

<nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Chapter context">
  {/* M-UX-REVIEW T4 D1 ‚Äî the in-breadcrumb `drawer-trigger` slot is
      gone. The trigger now mounts as a sibling of this breadcrumb
      in `Base.astro` (via Base's new `drawer-trigger` named slot)
      so it survives the breadcrumb-hide at <768px (UI-review F9).
      The slot itself is removed entirely (vs. left empty) because no
      consumer should be passing children to it post-T4 ‚Äî leaving it
      would silently swallow miswired markup. */}
  {currentChapter && currentCollection && (
    <>
      <div class="breadcrumb-path">
        <ol aria-label="Breadcrumb path">
          <li>
            {/* T9 D4 / AC7: cs-300 root is a real link to home. */}
            <a class="path-root" href={homeHref}>cs-300</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            {/* T9 D4 / AC9 + T3 D1: current chapter is a non-link
                <span> with aria-current="page". The middle path
                segment (Lectures / Notes / Practice link to the
                landing page) was REMOVED in T3 D1 ‚Äî the user reads
                the current collection from the segmented control
                under the H1 and the URL itself. The landing-page
                link is preserved via the new collection tabs
                (`CollectionTabs.astro`) and the home page card grid
                (T1 D1) ‚Äî see T3 spec "Out of scope" for the link-
                reachability analysis. */}
            <span class="path-current" aria-current="page">ch_{currentChapter.n} ‚Äî {currentChapter.subtitle}</span>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="breadcrumb-controls">
        {prevChapter ? (
          <a
            class="chapter-button prev"
            href={chapterHref(currentCollection, prevChapter.id)}
            rel="prev"
            aria-label={`Previous chapter: ch_${prevChapter.n} ‚Äî ${prevChapter.subtitle}`}
          >
            {/* T3 D1: arrow glyphs (‚Üê / ‚Üí) replace the cycle-1
                guillemets (‚Äπ / ‚Ä∫) per the UI-review F5 before/after
                mock. Same width, more obviously navigational on
                mobile. The functional test
                `breadcrumb-prev-next-arrows` asserts presence. */}
            <span aria-hidden="true">‚Üê</span>
            <span class="chapter-button-label">ch_{prevChapter.n}</span>
          </a>
        ) : (
          <span class="chapter-button prev is-disabled" aria-disabled="true">
            <span aria-hidden="true">‚Üê</span>
            <span class="chapter-button-label">prev</span>
          </span>
        )}

        {/* T3 D1: collection-switcher `<ul class="collection-switcher">`
            REMOVED. Hoisted to `CollectionTabs.astro` mounted directly
            under the chapter H1. The link contract (cross-collection
            navigation in one click) is preserved at that new home. */}

        {nextChapter ? (
          <a
            class="chapter-button next"
            href={chapterHref(currentCollection, nextChapter.id)}
            rel="next"
            aria-label={`Next chapter: ch_${nextChapter.n} ‚Äî ${nextChapter.subtitle}`}
          >
            <span class="chapter-button-label">ch_{nextChapter.n}</span>
            <span aria-hidden="true">‚Üí</span>
          </a>
        ) : (
          <span class="chapter-button next is-disabled" aria-disabled="true">
            <span class="chapter-button-label">next</span>
            <span aria-hidden="true">‚Üí</span>
          </span>
        )}
      </div>
    </>
  )}
</nav>

<style>
  /* Scoped styles; tokens come from src/styles/chrome.css (imported
     globally by Base.astro). The Base.astro `[data-slot="breadcrumb"]`
     wrapper supplies the bottom border, the surface background, AND
     the sticky positioning (`position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 50`
     moved out of this inner nav at T8 cycle 1 per M-UX-T3-ISS-01 ‚Äî
     the outer slot wrapper has the real stick range because it's a
     direct grid child of `.chrome` (`min-height: 100vh` + tall page
     content). This inner `.breadcrumb` only owns the row layout. */

  .breadcrumb {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--mux-space-3);
    padding: var(--mux-space-2) var(--mux-space-4);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  .breadcrumb-path ol {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--mux-space-2);
  }

  .breadcrumb-path li {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--mux-space-2);
  }

  /* Slash separator between path segments ‚Äî pure CSS so no extra
     <span class="sep"> markup is needed. Skip the first item. */
  .breadcrumb-path li + li::before {
    content: '/';
    color: var(--mux-fg-subtle);
  }

  .breadcrumb-path a {
    color: var(--mux-fg-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .breadcrumb-path a:hover {
    color: var(--mux-fg);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  /* T9 D4 ‚Äî `.path-root` is now an <a>; the .breadcrumb-path a rule
     above handles the muted color + hover/underline behaviour. We
     keep this rule for the de-emphasised subtle tone the cycle-1
     <span> had so the leading crumb stays visually quieter than the
     middle "Lectures" segment. */
  a.path-root {
    color: var(--mux-fg-subtle);
  }

  .path-current {
    color: var(--mux-fg);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .breadcrumb-controls {
    /* Push controls to the right of the path on wide widths; on narrow
       widths the wrap drops them onto the next row. */
    margin-left: auto;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--mux-space-2);
  }

  /* T3 D1 (2026-04-27): the `.collection-switcher` + `.collection-pill`
     rules were removed alongside the collection-switcher markup. The
     equivalent visual treatment lives on `.collection-tab` /
     `.collection-tab.is-current` in `CollectionTabs.astro`. */

  .chapter-button {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--mux-space-1);
    padding: 2px var(--mux-space-3);
    border: 1px solid var(--mux-border-subtle);
    border-radius: 4px;
    color: var(--mux-fg-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    background: var(--mux-surface);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .chapter-button:hover {
    background: var(--mux-surface-alt);
    color: var(--mux-fg);
  }

  .chapter-button.is-disabled {
    color: var(--mux-fg-subtle);
    background: var(--mux-surface-alt);
    cursor: not-allowed;
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  .chapter-button-label {
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  }
</style>
